I have a custom CSS item: .fullScrCkeditor .ck-editor__editable {
height: 600px;
} I want to dynamically change it’s height. For example, when the component used this item is rendered I want it first check the dialog’s height and then put the height in fullScrCkeditor as 65% of the dialog’s height. How can I do this?

You can achieve this by using JavaScript to calculate the height of the dialog and set the height of the `.fullScrCkeditor .ck-editor__editable` element dynamically. Here's an example code snippet to accomplish this:

```javascript
// Get the height of the dialog
var dialogHeight = sap.ui.getCore().byId("dialogId").$().height(); 

// Calculate 65% of the dialog height
var newHeight = dialogHeight * 0.65;

// Set the new height value in CSS
$(".fullScrCkeditor .ck-editor__editable").css("height", newHeight + "px");
```

In this code snippet:
- Replace `"dialogId"` with the actual ID of your dialog component.
- The code calculates 65% of the dialog's height and sets it as the height of the `.fullScrCkeditor .ck-editor__editable` element using jQuery.

You can place this code snippet in the `onAfterRendering` method of your dialog component to dynamically set the height of the desired element when the component is rendered.

