No, it's best not to create redirects within `handleRegistration`. Instead, you can `return` a Promise from `handleRegistration` that resolves with the user data or rejects with an error message.

Then, you can call `handleRegistration`, wait for the Promise to resolve or reject, and redirect the user based on the result.

Here's an updated version of `handleRegistration`:

```
const handleRegistration = () => {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    if (
      name === '' ||
      surname === '' ||
      email === '' ||
      phone === '' ||
      password === '' ||
      confirmPassword === ''
    ) {
      reject('Пожалуйста, заполните все поля для регистрации');
      return;
    }
    if (password !== confirmPassword) {
      reject('Пароли не совпадают');
      return;
    }
    firebase
      .auth()
      .createUserWithEmailAndPassword(email, password)
      .then((result) => {
        const userDetails = {
          name,
          surname,
          email,
          phone,
        };
        firebase.database().ref(`users/${result.user.uid}`).set(userDetails);
        resolve(userDetails);
      })
      .catch((error) => {
        reject(error.message);
      });
  });
};
```

